ProtoTheorem:
. "A sequence $\{\mathbf{X}_r\}$ in $\R^n$ converges if and 
   only if for each $\epsilon>0$ there is an integer $K$ such 
   that $$ |\mathbf{X}_r-\mathbf{X}_s|<\epsilon \quad if\quad 
   r,s\ge K. $$"
Metadata:
. name: "Cauchy's Convergence Criterion"
